The difficulties are already beginning to show. I will probably have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUSLY long and require A LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and for now, it seems *completely* manageable to me. It's just that it will take a lot of time and money.
In case the challenge awaiting me interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. It doesn't issue a medical certificate if you're undergoing treatment for it.
